org.eclipse.viatra.transformation.views.traceability.patterns

Class Trace2paramMatch

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.api.impl.BasePatternMatch
      • org.eclipse.viatra.transformation.views.traceability.patterns.Trace2paramMatch
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.api.IPatternMatch

    public abstract class Trace2paramMatch
extends org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.api.impl.BasePatternMatch
    Pattern-specific match representation of the org.eclipse.viatra.transformation.views.traceability.patterns.trace2param pattern, to be used in conjunction with Trace2paramMatcher.

    Class fields correspond to parameters of the pattern. Fields with value null are considered unassigned. Each instance is a (possibly partial) substitution of pattern parameters, usable to represent a match of the pattern in the result of a query, or to specify the bound (fixed) input parameters when issuing a query.

    See Also:
    Trace2paramMatcher, Trace2paramProcessor

      • newMatch

        public static Trace2paramMatch newMatch(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject pParam,
                        Trace pTrace,
                        java.lang.String pId)
        Returns a new (partial) match. This can be used e.g. to call the matcher with a partial match.

        The returned match will be immutable. Use newEmptyMatch() to obtain a mutable match object.

        Parameters:
        pParam - the fixed value of pattern parameter param, or null if not bound.
        pTrace - the fixed value of pattern parameter trace, or null if not bound.
        pId - the fixed value of pattern parameter id, or null if not bound.
        Returns:
        the (partial) match object.
